pullRequest.title: Enable JIT testing for value types tests
pullRequest.bodyText:
This change adds a variation to test with JIT compilation forced on with count=1,disableAsyncCompilation.
This is marked as  a work-in-progress as tests that depends on pull request #8922 and pull request #9128 currently fail:

 Pull request #8922
 Pull request #9128

nodes.bodyText: We should also add invocationCount = 2 and add an -Xjit:count=1,disableAsyncCompilation test as that is more realistic once we can inline methods.

afterCommit.message:

compilation scenarios a little more realistic.

commit.message:
Enable JIT testing for value types tests

This change adds an invocationCount of 2 to the value type tests, along
with a new test case name to invoke those same tests with a new test
variation that has JIT compilation enabled with
-Xjit:count=1,disableAsyncCompilation.

Signed-off-by:  Henry Zongaro <zongaro@ca.ibm.com>
